1	Corporate average fuel economy - Wikipedia	The Corporate Average Fuel Economy (CAFE) standards are regulations in the  United States, first enacted by the United States Congress in 1975, after the 1973 -74 Arab Oil Embargo, to improve the average fuel economy of cars and light  trucks (trucks, vans and sport utility vehicles) produced for sale in the United  States.	https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Corporate_average_fuel_economy
